long_definition: ܗܽܘ he; ܗܽܘ ܟܰܕ ܗܽܘ the same.
ܗܘܳܐ fut. ܢܶܗܘܶܐ, (apocopated ܢܗܶܐ) Ia to be, to become; to exist; to take place, to happen; + ܠ‍ to have; IIIa to bring into existence; IIIp.
ܠܳܐ not, no; (in compounds) in-, un-.
ܡܶܢ from, out of, on; by, as a result of; on the part of; than; some of, out of.
ܗܳܢܳܐ, ܗܳܢ this (m); ܗܳܢܳܐ ܟܽܠܶܗ so very, to such a degree.
ܥܰܠ upon, on, above, against, opposite, by, about, concerning, over.
ܟܽܠ, ܟܽܘܠ, ܟܽܘܠܳܐ all, the whole; ܟܠ +(absolute noun) every, each (e.g. ܟܽܠܝܽܘܡ every, each day).
ܐܶܡܰܪ fut. ܢܺܐܡܰܪ, Ia to say, speak; Ip.
ܟܰܕ when, while; ܗܽܘ ܟܰܕ ܗܽܘ the same; ܕܺܝܠܶܗ ܟܰܕ ܕܺܝܠܶܗ by the same; ܟܰܕ ܛܳܒ although.
ܡܳܪܝܳܐ Lord; lord, master, ruler; ܡܳܪܶܐ master of, owner of, endowed with; + ܚܰܘܒܳܐ creditor.
ܐܺܝܬ there is, exists; + -ܕ some; + -ܠ‍‍ to have.
ܐܰܝܟ as, like, according to; -ܐܰܝܟ ܕ so that.
ܡܶܛܽܠ because of, on account of, on behalf of, concerning; -ܡܶܛܽܠ ܕ because, so that.
ܗܰܘ that (m.); -ܐܰܝܟ ܗܰܘ ܕ as though.
ܗܳܝ that (f.); -ܒܗܳܝ ܕ in that…, because.

ܒܪܳܐ (pl. ܒܢܰܝ̈ܳܐ), f. ܒܰܪܬܳܐ (pl. ܒܢ̈ܳܬܳܐ) son, daughter. Many phrases with ܒܰܪ, ܒܰܪܬ, ܒܢ̈ܰܝ, ܒܢ̈ܳܬ expressing relationship, belonging; e.g.: ܒܰܪ ܐܶܓܳܪܳܐ lunatic; ܒܰܪ ܐܺܝܬܽܘܬܳܐ consubstantial; ܒܰܪ ܐܢܳܫܳܐ, ܒܰܪܢܳܫܳܐ person, human being; ܒܰܪ ܐܰܬܪܳܐ compatriot, indigenous; ܒܰܪ ܒܰܝܬܳܐ bond slave, born in the house; human being, kindred; ܒܰܪ ܒܶܣܬܪܳܐܺܝܬ backwards; ܒܰܪ ܒܶܣܬܪܳܝܳܐ reverse; ܒܰܪ ܓܰܒܳܐ adherent (of a party, sect); ܒܰܪ ܓܶܢܣܳܐ kindred; ܒܰܪ ܙܰܘܓܳܐ husband; close companion; ܒܰܪܬ ܙܰܘܓܳܐ wife; ܒܰܪ ܚܺܐܪ̈ܶܐ noble, freeborn; ܒܰܪ ܟܝܳܢܳܐ consubstantial, of the same nature; ܒܰܪ ܠܘܺܝܬܳܐ travelling companion; ܒܰܪ ܡܕܺܝܢ̱ܬܳܐ citizen; ܒܰܪ ܡܶܠܟܳܐ counselor; ܒܰܪ ܥܳܠܡܳܐ layman; ܒܰܪ ܥܶܢܝܳܢܳܐ familiar friend; ܒܰܪ ܦܶܚܡܳܐ similar, Kth. colleague; ܒܰܪ ܩܝܳܡܳܐ / ܒܰܪ̱ܬ ܩܝܳܡܳܐ someone who has taken ascetic vows; Kth. f. wife of a priest; ܒܰܪ ܫܡܳܐ having the same name, namesake; ܒܰܪ ܫܳܥܬܳܐ, ܒܰܪ ܫܳܥܬܶܗ immediately.
ܥܰܡ with, at, on; besides; along.
ܚܰܕ one; a certain; each; one…the other; ܚܰܕ ܠܚܰܕ one another; ܚܰܕ ܒܫܰܒܥܳܐ seven times, sevenfold; ܚܰܕ ܟܡܳܐ how much more; ܒܰܚܕܳܐ at once, directly; ܡܶܢ ܚܕܳܐ, ܡܶܚܕܳܐ suddenly.
ܐ̱ܢܳܫܳܐ person, human being; relations; people. ܐ̱ܢܳܫ someone, a certain; ܒܰܪ ܐ̱ܢܳܫ̈ܳܐ, pl. ܒ̈ܢܰܝ ܐ̱ܢܳܫ̈ܳܐ a person, human being; ܟܽܠ ܐ̱ܢܳܫ everyone.
ܐܶܠܳܐ if not, unless; except, but.
ܠܘܳܬ to, towards, with, near; with respect to.
ܚܙܳܐ fut. ܢܶܚܙܶܐ, Ia to see, perceive; Ip; to be seen, be visible, to appear.
ܩܰܕܺܝܫܳܐ holy, sacred; saint; ܪܽܘܚܳܐ ܩܰܕܺܝܫܳܐ Holy Spirit.
ܗܺܝ she; ܗܺܝ ܟܰܕ ܗܺܝ the same.
ܐܰܝܢܳܐ, f. ܐܰܝܕܳܐ, pl. ܐܰܝܠܶܝܢ who?, which? what?; + -ܕ he who.
ܐܶܬܳܐ fut. ܢܺܐܬܶܐ, imp. ܬܳܐ (f. ܬܳܝ) Ia to come, arrive; IIIa ܐܰܝܬܺܝ to bring, introduce; IIIp.
-ܕܺܝܠ‍ of, own; ܕܺܝܠܶܗ ܟܰܕ ܕܺܝܠܶܗ by the same.
ܥܒܰܕ fut. ܢܶܥܒܶܕ, Ia to do, make, perform, work; Ip; IIIa to prompt, to induce; to effect; IIIp.

ܐܺܝܕܳܐ (pl. ܐܺܝ̈ܕܶܐ, ܐܺܝܕܰܝ̈ܳܐ) f. hand; handle, etc; ܝܰܕ edge, side; ܒܝܰܕ through, by means of, with the help of; -ܒܝܰܕ ܕ because; ܡܶܢ ܝܰܕ on account of; ܥܰܠ ܝܰܕ beside; ܒܺܐܝܕܳܐ ܒܺܐܝܕܳܐ little by little; partly.
ܥܳܠܡܳܐ age; eternity; world; ܠܥܳܠܰܡ forever.
ܚܢܰܢ we. (can also be written ܚ̱ܢܰܢ or ܐܶܢܰܚܢܰܢ)
ܡܶܠܬܳܐ (pl. ܡ̈ܶܠܐ) f. word, saying, sentence; matter, affair; Gram. verb; m. the Word (God).

ܒܰܝܬܳܐ (pl. ܒ̈ܳܬܶܐ) m. house; home, room; stanza, verse. ܒܶܝܬ + (name) family, dynasty, generation; church (+ saint’s name); territory. Many other phrases with ܒܶܝܬ e.g., ܒܶܝܬ ܐܺܝܩܳܪܳܐ latrine; ܒܶܝܬ ܐܰܣܝܪ̈ܶܐ prison; ܒܶܝܬ ܐܰܦܽܘܣܺܝܰܐ latrine; ܒܶܝܬ ܐܰܪ̈ܟܶܐ archive, library; ܒܶܝܬ ܒܽܘܫܳܠܳܐ kitchen; ܒܶܝܬ ܒܰܘܬܳܐ night lodging; ܒܶܝܬ ܒܳܟ̈ܶܐ lamentation; ܒܶܝܬ ܓܰܘܣܳܐ refuge; ܒܶܝܬ ܓܰܙܳܐ treasury, Lit. West Syriac book of liturgical tunes; ܒܶܝܬ ܕܰܘܩܳܐ watch tower; ܒܶܝܬ ܕܺܝܢܳܐ law court; ܒܶܝܬ ܕܡܳܟܳܐ Kth. hotel, hostel, guesthouse; ܒܶܝܬ ܘܳܠܺܝܬܳܐ toilet; ܒܶܝܬ ܘܰܥܕܳܐ meeting place; ܒܶܝܬ ܛܒܳܚܳܐ kitchen; ܒܶܝܬ ܝܰܠܕܳܐ the Nativity, Christmas, birthday, horoscope; ܒܶܝܬ ܝܰܠܕܽܘܬܳܐ birthday; ܒܶܝܬ ܟܢܽܘܫܬܳܐ synagogue; school; ܒܶܝܬ ܟܪ̈ܺܝܗܶܐ hospital; ܒܶܝܬ ܟܬܳܒ̈ܶܐ library; ܒܶܝܬ ܡܰܘܬܒ̈ܶܐ historical and some wisdom books of the Bible; ܒܶܝܬ ܡܰܝ̈ܳܐ latrine; ܒܶܝܬ ܡܺܝ̈ܬܶܐ place of the dead, the grave, Sheol; ܒܶܝܬ ܡܰܥܡܽܘܕܺܝܬܳܐ baptistery; ܒܶܝܬ ܡܰܥܪܦܳܐ Kth. bank (financial); ܒܶܝܬ ܡܰܪܕܽܘܬܳܐ place of teaching, school; ܒܶܝܬ ܡܰܫܪܝܳܐ resting place, lodging; ܒܶܝܬ ܡܶܫܬܽܘܬܳܐ banquet; ܒܶܝܬ ܣܳܗ̈ܕܶܐ martyrium, chapel; ܒܶܝܬ ܣܶܦܪܳܐ school; ܒܶܝܬ ܥܶܕܳܢ̈ܶܐ records office; ܒܶܝܬ ܥܰܝܢܳܐ forehead; ܒܶܝܬ ܥܳܠܡܳܐ sepulcher; ܒܶܝܬ ܨܰܘܒܳܐ rendezvous, meeting place; Kth. college, university; ܒܶܝܬ ܨܠܽܘܬܳܐ place of prayer (usually a summer altar in the church’s courtyard); ܒܶܝܬ ܩܒܽܘܪܳܐ cemetery; ܒܶܝܬ ܩܰܕܺܝ̈ܫܶܐ place of burial for bishops and saints; ܒܶܝܬ ܩܽܘܕܫܳܐ sanctuary; ܒܶܝܬ ܩܦܳܣܳܐ granary; ܒܶܝܬ ܪܰܚܝܳܐ mill; ܒܶܝܬ ܫܰܒܬܳܐ synagogue, refectory; ܒܶܝܬ ܬܚܽܘ̈ܡܶܐ border-lands.
ܢܰܦܫܳܐ (pl. ܢܰܦ̈ܫܳܬܳܐ) f. soul; vital principal, life; living person; funeral stele; ܢܰܦܫܶܗ etc. himself etc.; ܡܶܢ ܢܰܦܫܶܗ of his own accord.
ܡܶܕܶܡ (pl. ܡܶܕ̈ܶܡܶܐ) thing, affair; something; a certain.
ܝܰܗ̱ܒ fut. ܢܶܬܶܠ, Ia to give, to grant; to allow, permit; to yield; to put, place; to entrust, commit; Ip to be given, granted; to be permitted; to be given up, delivered.
ܐܰܒ݂ܳܐ father; spiritual father; (pl. ܐܰܒ̈ܳܗܶܐ) parents, forefathers; (pl. ܐܰܒ̈ܳܗܳܬܳܐ) spiritual fathers.
ܪܽܘܚܳܐ (pl. ܪ̈ܽܘܚܶܐ, ܪ̈ܽܘܚܳܬܳܐ) f. (usually m. in prose for Holy Spirit) spirit; wind; ܪܽܘܚܳܐ ܕܩܽܘܕܫܳܐ, ܪܽܘܚܳܐ ܩܰܕܺܝܫܳܐ Holy Spirit.
ܝܰܘܡܳܐ (pl. ܝܰܘ̈ܡܶܐ, ܝܰܘ̈ܡܳܬܳܐ) m. day, day time.
ܩܳܡ fut. ܢܩܽܘܡ, Ia to arise, stand; to last; to be extant; to stop; Ip to e constituted; IIa to establish; IIp; IIIa to raise up, establish.
English: to stand; to start; to stop

long_definition: ܐ̱ܚܪܺܢܳܐ, ܐ̱ܚܪܺܝܬܳܐ, ܐ̱ܚܪ̈ܳܢܶܐ, ܐ̱ܚܪ̈ܳܢܝܳܬܳܐ other, another; next; Kth. ܙܢܳܐ ܐ̱ܚܪܺܢܳܐ Lit. alternative (melody).

ܝܺܕܰܥ fut. ܢܶܕܰܥ, Ia to know, perceive, understand; Ip to be known, understood; to become known, become famous, to flourish; to be known as; to be made known, to be meant; IIa to inform, indicate; IIIa ܐܰܘܕܰܥ to make known, to inform, announce;IIIp.
ܐܰܝܟܰܢܳܐ how?, as; + -ܕ so that; ܕܰܐܝܟ ܐܰܝܟܰܢܳܐ for example.
ܗܳܟܰܢ, ܗܳܟܰܢܳܐ thus, in like manner; such.
ܐܰܪܥܳܐ (pl. ܐܰܪ̈ܥܳܬܳܐ) f. earth, land; Kth. ground, floor.
ܪܰܒܳܐ great, large; grand; teacher; eldest; prefect; magnate; ܪܰܒ + chief-, arch-.
ܡܳܐ what; how! -ܡܳܐ ܕ that which; when;-ܟܠ ܡܳܐ ܕ whatsoever, whensoever.
ܙܰܒܢܳܐ time, season; ܒܰܙܒܰܢ sometimes; ܒܟܽܠܙܒܰܢ always; ܟܡܳܐ ܙܰܒܢܺܝ̈ܢ often.
ܥܰܡܳܐ (pl. ܥܰܡ̱̈ܡܶܐ) people, nation; populace; ܥܰܡ̱̈ܡܶܐ gentiles, pagans; paternal uncle.
ܛܳܒܳܐ good, excellent; precious (of stone); cultivated (of plant).
ܫܽܘܒܚܳܐ praise, glory; splendor; opinion, tenet.
ܫܡܳܐ (pl. ܫ̈ܡܳܗܶܐ, ܫ̈ܡܳܗܳܬܳܐ) m. name, title; pretext; reputation; Gram. noun, part of speech.
ܒܳܬܰܪ after; ܒܳܬܰܪ ܪܺܝܫܶܗ upside-down; ܒܳܬܰܪ ܒܳܬܰܪ one by one.
ܚܰܝܠܳܐ (pl. ܚܰܝ̈ܠܶܐ, ܚܰܝ̈ܠܰܘܳܬܳܐ) m. might, strength, power; miracle; army, host; sense, meaning; faculty, instinct; wealth; ܒܚܰܝܠܳܐ virtually.
ܩܪܳܐ 1 fut. ܢܶܩܪܶܐ, Ia to call, summon, invite, invoke; Kth. to read; Ip.
ܩܳܠܳܐ voice, sound; expression; hymn; tune; ܒܰܪܬ ܩܳܠܳܐ expression, quotation, Gram. word.
ܟܝܳܢܳܐ nature; natural disposition; substance; creature.
ܡܳܢ, ܡܳܢܳܐ what? ܠܡܳܢܳܐ, ܡܶܛܽܠ ܡܳܢܳܐ, ܥܰܠ ܡܳܢܳܐ why, wherefore?
ܥܰܠ fut. ܢܶܥܽܘܠ, Ia to enter, go in; IIp ܐܶܬܥܰܠܰܠ to be brought in, introduced; to make a pretext; to allege; to complain; IIIa ܐܰܥܶܠ to bring in, to introduce; to produce; IIIp.
ܪܺܝܫܳܐ, ܪܺܫܳܐ head; top; heading; beginning; (many phrases with ܪܺܝܫ head-, chief-); Kth. -ܟܺܐܒܳܐ ܕ headache.

ܫܪܳܐ fut. ܢܶܫܪܶܐ, Ia to loosen, unfasten; to release, let go; to repudiate; to absolve; to violate, break (law etc.); to dissolve; to confute; to reside, to dwell, to camp; to disband; to come to an end; Ip to be loosed, opened; to be paralyzed; to be released, dismissed; to disband, to break up; to be absolved; to be violated (law etc.); to be dissolved; to weigh anchor; IIa to begin; to weaken; to abolish; IIp to be begun; to be paralyzed; to be destroyed; to dine; IIIa to call a halt; to make to reside; to instill.
ܫܟܚ* ܐܶܫܟܰܚ fut. ܢܶܫܟܰܚ, Ia to find, to discover; to be able; Ip to be present, to happen; to be discovered, detected.
English: to find, to discover; to be able

long_definition: ܒܥܳܐ fut. ܢܶܒܥܶܐ, Ia to seek, desire, beseech; Ip to be necessary, required.
ܫܡܰܝܳܐ f. (and pl.) heaven; ceiling, roof.
ܩܒܰܠ fut. ܢܶܩܒܽܘܠ, Ia to accuse, complain of; to meet; to oppose; to appeal to; Ip to be accused; IIa to receive, accept; + ܛܰܝܒܽܘܬܳܐ to thank; IIp; IIIa to face; to meet.
ܫܡܰܥ fut. ܢܶܫܡܰܥ, Ia to hear, listen, understand, obey; Ip to be heard; to be obedient; IIIa to cause to hear; to tell, announce.

ܢܦܰܩ fut. ܢܶܦܽܘܩ, Ia to go out, depart, to issue; to turn out, come to pass; to be translated; to be expended; + ܒܪܽܘܚܳܐ to defend, excuse oneself; IIa to spend; to go through; to train, instruct; to expose; IIp to be trained, instructed, practiced; IIIa ܐܰܦܶܩ to bring out, produce; to remove; to repudiate; to spend; to send forth, to issue, to publish; to translate; to subtract; IIIp to be extracted, translated, pronounced.
English: to go out; to turn out

long_definition: ܡܰܢ indeed, on the one hand.
ܒܰܪܢܳܫܳܐ (also ܒܰܪ ܐ̱ܢܳܫܳܐ) human being, person.
ܣܳܡ fut. ܢܣܺܝܡ, Ia to set, put, place; to appoint; to constitute; ܣܳܡ ܒܪܶܥܝܳܢܳܐ to resolve; ܣܳܡ ܒܪܺܝܫܳܐ to punish; Ip; IIa ܣܰܝܶܡ to point (a text); IIp.
ܐܶܙܰܠ fut. ܢܺܐܙܰܠ, imp. ܙܶܠ, Ia to go; ܐܳܙܶܠ fit for, good for.
ܨܒܳܐ fut. ܢܶܨܒܶܐ, Ia to be willing, wish, want; + ܒ‍ to be pleased with; Ip to consent; + ܒ‍ to take pleasure in; IIIa to will.
English: to be willing; to be pleased with

long_definition: ܩܪܶܒ fut. ܢܶܩܪܽܘܒ, Ia to come near, approach; + ܒ‍ to touch; + ܥܰܡ to contend with; IIa to bring near; to offer; IIp to approach; to be presented, offered; IIIa to join battle, fight; IIIp.
ܚܰܘܺܝ IIa to show, manifest, demonstrate, make manifest; to issue (coinage); IIp.
ܐܰܬܪܳܐ, ܐܰܬܪ̈ܰܘܳܬܳܐ place, location, region, district; Kth. homeland; topic; opportunity;-ܐܰܬܰܪ ܕ where.
ܚܠܳܦ instead of, because of, in place of, on account of.
ܛܰܝܒܽܘܬܳܐ grace, kindness, favor; ܩܰܒܶܠ ܛܰܝܒܽܘܬܳܐ to be grateful, thankful; ܩܽܘܒܳܠ ܛܰܝܒܽܘܬܳܐ gratitude, thankfulness.
ܡܠܳܐ fut. ܢܶܡܠܶܐ, Ia to fill, complete; to be full; Ip to be filled, completed; IIa to fill up, fulfill, complete; IIp; III to fill up.
ܢܣܰܒ fut. ܢܶܣܰܒ, Ia to take, receive; + ܒ̈ܢܶܫܶܐ to marry; + ܒܰܐܦ̈ܶܐ to favor; to be a hypocrite; Ip.
ܫܰܒܰܚ IIa to praise, glorify; to hold an opinion; Lit. to sing the Gloria; IIp.
English: to praise; Lit. to sing the Gloria

long_definition: ܡܨܳܐ 2 fut. ܢܶܡܨܶܐ, Ia pass. part. ܡܨܶܐ to be able, capable; Ip to be able, prevail over; to resist.
ܡܰܠܟܽܘܬܳܐ rule, reign, kingdom, royal dignity.
ܓܰܘ , ܠܓܰܘ ܡܶܢ, ܒܓܰܘ inside, within. ܒܓܰܘ inside (see ܓܰܘ).
ܡܰܠܶܠ IIa to speak, talk; ܡܡܰܠܶܠ ܐܰܠܳܗܝ̈ܳܬܳܐ theologian; ܡܡܰܠܶܠ ܟܝܳܢ̈ܝܳܬܳܐ physiologist etc.; IIp to be spoken, told, said.
ܒܪܳܐ fut. ܢܶܒܪܶܐ, Ia to create
ܚܰܫܳܐ suffering, pain; sorrow, sadness; passion, affection; the Passion.
ܠܶܒܳܐ (pl. ܠܶܒܰܘ̈ܳܬܳܐ) m. heart; midst + ܕܠܳܐ senseless, without understanding; ܠܶܒܳܐ ܕܚܶܛܬܳܐ starch.
ܟܠܳܐ fut. ܢܶܟܠܶܐ, Ia to hinder, hold back; to prohibit; Ip to refuse, refrain; to be hindered, prohibited; IIa, IIIa = Ia.

ܝܺܠܶܕ fut. ܢܺܐܠܰܕ, Ia to give birth to, to bear; to beget, generate; Ip; IIp to help to give birth; IIIa to beget, procreate, bring forth; to effect, cause; IIIp to be helped by a midwife; to be brought to birth.
English: to give birth to; to beget

long_definition: ܟܬܰܒ fut. ܢܶܟܬܽܘܒ, Ia to write, copy out; to inscribe; to be written, put in writing; to be enrolled; to be described; IIIa to write (a book); to commit to writing, to record; to have something written; to dictate; to ascribe to.
ܚܝܳܐ fut. ܢܺܐܚܶܐ & ܢܺܚܶܐ, imp. ܚܝܺܝ, Ia to live, be alive, revive; to be saved; IIIa to give life, keep alive, save alive, bring to life; to save; IIIp.
ܕܡܳܐ blood, bloodshed; sap, juice (of plants).
ܪܚܶܡ fut. ܢܶܪܚܰܡ, Ia to love, to delight in; IIa, IIp to have mercy (on); IIIa to show love; to obtain a favor.
ܝܰܬܺܝܪܳܐ surpassing, abundant, especial; superfluous, excessive.
ܫܠܺܝܚܳܐ messenger, emissary; apostle; the Epistles (of Paul the Apostle); naked, stripped.
ܬܶܫܒܽܘܚܬܳܐ (pl. ܬܶܫܒ̈ܚܳܬܳܐ) praise, glory, magnificence; canticle.
ܐ̱ܪܳܙܳܐ (= ܪܳܐܙܳܐ) symbol, mystery, secret; pl. ܐ̱ܪ̈ܳܙܶܐ (liturgical) Mysteries. (See further under -ܪܐܙ).

ܝܕܐ* IIIa ܐܰܘܕܺܝ to confess, acknowledge; to profess, assert; to believe; to give thanks (to); IIIp to be acknowledged, recognized; to be confessed; to be praised; IVp ܐܶܫܬܰܘܕܺܝ to confess; to consent; + ܥܰܡ to make alliance with.
English: to confess; to believe; to give thanks (to)

long_definition: ܫܒܰܩ fut. ܢܶܫܒܽܘܩ, Ia to leave, to leave behind; to dismiss, repudiate; to permit; to forgive, remit; to forsake, to omit, to leave out; Ip to be left, deserted, repudiated, forgiven, passed over, deferred.
English: to forgive; to permit; to dismiss

long_definition: ܠܽܘܩܒܰܠ opposite, against; in front of, facing, towards; according to, in comparison.
ܟܡܳܐ how much, how many; + -ܕ as much as, as long as; ܟܡܳܐ ܙܰܒܢܺܝ̈ܢ sometimes, often enough.

ܥܰܝܢܳܐ f. eye (pl. ܥܰܝ̈ܢܶܐ); source, spring (pl. ܥܰܝ̈ܢܳܬܳܐ); arch (of bridge); brightness; surface; bud; ܒܶܝܬ ܥܰܝ̈ܢܶܐ forehead; ܒܥܰܝ̈ܢܰܝ in sight of, before; ܠܥܰܝ̈ܢܰܝ ܠܥܺܝܢ in the sight of; ܥܺܝܢ ܥܶܓܠܳܐ sardonyx.
ܐܽܘܪܚܳܐ (pl. ܐܽܘܪ̈ܚܳܬܳܐ) f. road, street, way, journey; manner; ܚܕܳܐ ܐܽܘܪܚܳܐ once and for all.

ܢܛܰܪ fut. ܢܶܛܰܪ rare ܢܶܛܽܘܪ, Ia to guard, watch, keep, preserve, retain; Ip to be guarded; to be observed; to be retained; to abstain from; ܢܳܛܰܪ ܟܽܘܪܣܺܝ, ܢܳܛܰܪ ܟܽܘܪܣܝܳܐ ‘keeper of the see’ (Patriarchal-candidate from birth in the hereditary system of the Church of the East); Kth. ܢܳܛܰܪ ܐ̱ܪܳܙܳܐ secretary; IIa to keep safe, to take care of; IIIa to put in a safe place, to preserve, to entrust.
ܡܺܝܬ fut. ܢܡܽܘܬ, Ia to die; Ip to be put to death; IIIa to put to death, kill; to mortify.
ܫܰܪܺܝܪܳܐ true, solid, sound, valid; officer, official.
ܫܰܪܟܳܐ remnant, rest; ܘܫܰܪܟܳܐ, ܘܰܕܫܰܪܟܳܐ etc.
ܙܕܩ Ia ܙܳܕܶܩ it is right, fitting; IIa to justify, declare righteous; to verify; to give alms; to assign; IIp.
ܛܽܘܒܳܐ good, good things; beatitude, bliss; ܛܽܘ̈ܒܶܐ the Beatitudes; ܛܽܘܒܰܝ̈ܟ blessed are you (etc.).

ܫܘܳܐ fut. ܢܶܫܘܶܐ, Ia to be even, equal; to be worth, worthy; to agree with; -ܫܘܶܐ ܒ‍ co-, fellow-; ܫܘܶܐ ܒܽܐܘܣܺܝܰܐ consubstantial; Ip to be held worthy; to agree; to unite, come together; IIa to spread out (rug etc.); to smooth; to wipe; to treat as equal; IIp; IIIa to level, to smooth; to hold equal; to consider worthy.
English: to be even; to be worthy; to agree with

long_definition: ܩܽܘܕܫܳܐ holiness; holy things; sanctuary; consecration; ܪܽܘܚܳܐ ܕܩܽܘܕܫܳܐ Holy Spirit.

ܥܒܰܪ fut. ܢܶܥܒܰܪ, Ia to pass on, pass by, to cross; to transgress; to surpass; Ip; IIIa to transfer, to remove; to pass over, to remit; to convert; to omit; to defer; IIIp to be translated, removed, transferred.
English: to cross; to transgress; to surpass

long_definition: ܢܳܡܽܘܣܳܐ law, custom, usage; the Law (Pentateuch).
ܨܶܐܕ (= ܨܶܝܕ) towards, to, with. ܨܶܝܕ (= ܨܶܐܕ) to, towards.
ܝܺܕܰܥܬܳܐ knowledge; understanding, apprehension; intelligence; indication; ܡܩܰܕܡܽܘܬ ܝܺܕܰܥܬܳܐ foreknowledge; prognosis.
ܦܩܰܕ fut. ܢܶܦܩܽܘܕ, Ia to command, order; to bid, instruct; to review, inspect; to inquire after, seek out; Ip to be missing, to be sought for; IIa to give a charge, order; IIp.

ܣܠܶܩ fut. ܢܶܣܰܩ, Ia to ascend, go up; to turn out, to succeed; IIa to lift up; to winnow; IIp to be lifted up; to ascend; IIIa ܐܰܣܶܩ to raise up, lift up, bring up; to pay tribute; to impose tribute; to emboss; to enhance.
English: to ascend; to turn out, to succeed

long_definition: ܝܺܠܶܦ Ia to learn; IIa ܐܰܠܶܦ to teach, train, instruct; IIp to be instructed; to inform oneself.

ܫܠܶܡ fut. ܢܶܫܠܰܡ, Ia to come to an end, to be concluded; to be complete; to agree with; to consent to, to concede; to approve; to adhere to; to resemble; Ip to be delivered up; to be in agreement; IIa to finish, to complete, to conclude; to fulfill; to repair, to restore; to recompense; to greet; to take leave of, to die; IIp to be completed, to be accomplished; to be surrendered, handed over; to be brought to a state of peace; IIIa to hand over, to commit; to give up, to surrender; to achieve, to finish; to transmit, hand down; IIIp to be handed over; to take possession of; to be handed down.
English: to come to an end; to be complete; to agree with

long_definition: ܕܡܽܘܬܳܐ likeness, form, shape, example, image, appearance.

ܫܩܰܠ fut. ܢܶܫܩܽܘܠ, Ia to lift; to carry, take, receive; to remove; + ܛܰܥܢܳܐ to take trouble, to undertake; Ip to be lifted up, taken up; to be captured (of town); to be abolished; IIa to raise, carry, sustain; IIp to be exalted; to prevail over; IIIa to set off, depart; to migrate, to immigrate.
English: to lift; to receive; to remove

long_definition: ܨܠܺܝܒܳܐ cross; sign of the cross.
ܒܪܶܟ, ܒܪܰܟ fut. ܢܶܒܪܰܟ & ܢܶܒܪܽܘܟ, Ia to kneel; IIa to bless, pronounce a blessing; IIp; IIIa to cause to kneel.
ܬܰܪܥܳܐ door, gate; gateway, approach; court; stanza, chapter; opening; mountain pass.
ܗܰܝܡܶܢ IVa to believe; to have faith in; to trust; IVp.
ܥܒܳܕܳܐ work, occupation; action; making, construction; possessions; province; ܒܰܥܒܳܕܳܐ in deed, in reality.
ܒܶܣܪܳܐ flesh; pulp (of fruit); Kth. meat.
ܢܚܶܬ fut. ܢܶܚܽܘܬ, Ia to go down, descend; Ip; IIa to bring down; to lower, to abase; IIp to lower oneself, to stoop down; IIIa ܐܰܚܶܬ to bring down, to take down, to cause to come down.

ܣܒܰܪ fut. ܢܶܣܒܰܪ, Ia to think, to believe, to suppose; Ip to be supposed, considered; IIa to hope, to trust (in); to announce, declare; IIp to be announced, proclaimed; to be considered; to seem; IIIa to think, suppose; to suspect; to profess to be.
English: to think, to believe, to suppose

long_definition: ܫܐܶܠ fut. ܢܶܫܰܐܠ, Ia to ask; to inquire; to borrow; Ip to excuse oneself; to decline; IIa to question, to interrogate; IIp; IIIa to lend.
ܦܢܳܐ fut. ܢܶܦܢܶܐ, Ia to turn, to return; Ip; IIa to restore; to return; to respond, answer, reply; IIp; IIIa to bring back; to convert; to turn.
ܝܺܡܳܐ fut. ܢܺܐܡܶܐ, Ia to swear, take an oath; IIIa ܐܰܘܡܺܝ to make to swear, bind by oath; to adjure, call to witness; to exorcize; IIIp to be put to oath; to be adjured; to be exorcized.
ܓܠܳܐ fut. ܢܶܓܠܶܐ, Ia to uncover, reveal, make known; Ip; IIa to uncover, disclose; to lead, go into captivity; IIp; IIIa to uncover.
ܩܢܽܘܡܳܐ being, self, substance; person; hypostasis; subsistence; proper characteristic.
ܐܶܡܳܐ (pl. ܐܶܡ̈ܗܳܬܳܐ, ܐܶܡ̈ܳܗܶܐ) f. mother, parent.
ܨܠܳܐ fut. ܢܶܨܠܶܐ, Ia to turn aside, incline; to set a trap; Ip to lean, incline; to be prone to, inclined to; IIa to pray; IIp to be offered in prayer.
English: to turn aside; to set a trap

long_definition: ܐܶܚܰܕ fut. ܢܶܐܚܽܘܕ, Ia to take, hold, seize; to hold, contain, possess; Ip to be taken, caught, held; to be closed, shut; IIa to shut, close, grasp; IIIa ܐܰܘܚܶܕ to kindle; to hand to; to let out.

ܢܦܰܠ fut. ܢܶܦܶܠ, Ia to fall, collapse; to lie down; to be thrown; to happen, occur, befall; to lapse; IIa to be thrown down, fling down; IIp to fall away, waste away, to diminish, to rot; IIIa ܐܰܦܶܠ to overthrow; to leave out; to cause to fall; to seduce.
ܥܶܠܬܳܐ, ܥܶܠ̈ܠܳܬܳܐ cause, pretext; rationale; affair, occasion; argument, heading.
ܛܰܠܝܳܐ (pl. ܛܠܳܝ̈ܶܐ) child, boy; young; servant.
ܫܰܢ̱ܬܳܐ (pl. ܫܢܰܝ̈ܳܐ) f. year; ܫܢܰܬ era of.
ܣܥܰܪ fut. ܢܶܣܥܽܘܪ, Ia to do, act, perform; to visit; to care for; to inspect; Ip; IIa to visit; to vow one’s hair; IIp to be achieved; IIIa to grow hair.
English: to do; to visit; to care for

long_definition: ܩܰܠܺܝܠܳܐ swift; light; ܩܰܠܺܝܠ a little, few; ܒܨܺܝܪ ܩܰܠܺܝܠ almost.
ܐܺܝܩܳܪܳܐ honor, glory; mark of honor, honorarium; margin (of book).

ܗܦܰܟ fut. ܢܶܗܦܽܘܟ, Ia to turn, to return; to change; to convert; to do again; Ip to turn around; to be changed; to be overthrown; IIa to turn, to change; to overthrow; IIp to go about; to conduct oneself; to be occupied; to be intimate with; IIIa to turn, to change; to restore; to overthrow; to upset; to refute.
English: to turn; to change; to do again

long_definition: ܙܥܽܘܪܳܐ small, little; younger; ܙܥܽܘܪ̈ܶܐ few; ܒܰܙܥܽܘܪ̈ܝܳܬܳܐ in brief.
ܩܢܳܐ fut. ܢܶܩܢܶܐ, Ia to acquire, possess; Ip; IIa to retain; to procure; IIp to acquire; IIIa to confer, bestow.
ܐܶܡܰܬܝ when? -ܟܽܠ ܐܶܡܰܬܝ ܕ. whenever; ܒܟܽܠ ܐܶܡܰܬܝ at all times, every time; ܐܺܝܬ ܐܶܡܰܬܝ sometimes.
ܣܽܘܥܪܳܢܳܐ act, deed, affair; fact, reality; Gram. object.

ܝܺܬܶܒ fut. ܢܶܬܶܒ, Ia to sit, sit down, be seated; to embark (on boat); to remain, abide; to settle; to dwell; to be situated; IIa to populate, cause to settle; IIp to be inhabited; to subside, settle down; to be populated; IIIa ܐܰܘܬܶܒ to cause to dwell, to settle; to restore; to appoint; IIIp to sojourn, to settle, to reside.
English: to sit; to embark (on boat); to remain

long_definition: ܙܢܳܐ species, variety, kind, manner. ܙܢܳܐ ܐ̱ܚܪܺܢܳܐ Lit. alternative (melody).
ܐܶܟܰܠ fut. ܢܶܐܟܽܘܠ, Ia to eat, to consume; to squander; + ܩܰܪ̈ܨܶܐ to slander, to accuse; Ip; IIIa ܐܰܘܟܶܠ to give to eat; IIIp.
English: to eat, to consume; to squander

long_definition: ܝܰܠܕܳܐ giving birth; birth, nativity; child, offspring, produce.
ܥܰܬܶܕ IIa to prepare, to make ready; IIp to get ready; to be ready, to be arranged.
ܩܛܰܠ fut. ܢܶܩܛܽܘܠ, Ia to kill; Ip; IIa to murder, slay; IIp.
ܓܶܢܣܳܐ (pl. ܓܶܢ̈ܣܶܐ , ܓܶܢ̈ܣܳܢܶܐ) family, race; species, kind; Gram. gender; ܓܢܶܣ ܓܢܶܣ various.
ܕܶܚܠܬܳܐ fear; reverence, worship; religion; object of fear, idol.

ܟܢܰܫ fut. ܢܶܟܢܽܘܫ, Ia to gather, assemble, collect; to sweep; to thicken (of a liquid); Ip to be gathered; to concur; IIa to assemble, collect together; to compile; to conclude; to reckon, make a computation; IIp.
ܗܰܘܢܳܐ intellect, mind, reason; sense, meaning.
ܫܰܝܢܳܐ peace, tranquility; truce; cultivated land; domesticated (animal).
ܚܰܕܬܳܐ, ܚܕܰܬܳܐ, ܚܰܕ̈ܬܶܐ, ܚܰܕ̈ܬܳܬܳܐ new, recent.
ܡܶܟܺܝܠ thence; and so, therefore; + ܠܳܐ no longer, no more.

ܡܠܰܟ fut. ܢܶܡܠܽܘܟ, Ia to counsel, advise, promise, reign; Ip to consult; to be promised; IIa to give advice; to promise; IIIa to counsel, give advice; to reign, rule; to make king; IIIp to be made king; to be reigned over.
ܚܳܪ fut. ܢܚܽܘܪ, Ia to look, behold, gaze at; to look for, expect; to regard, pay attention to; IIIa to cause to look; to direct (gaze etc.); to urge; to see.
English: to gaze at; to look for; to pay attention to

long_definition: ܐܰܦ̈ܶܐ f. face, countenance; ܠܰܐܦܰܝ̈ towards; ܥܰܠ ܐܰܦܰܝ̈ on behalf of; ܐܰܦܰܝ̈ ܬܰܪܥܳܐ curtain.

ܥܢܳܐ fut. ܢܶܥܢܶܐ, Ia to answer, respond; to converse; ܥܢܶܐ occupied (with); Ip to be heard; to be occupied, engaged; IIa to sing in alternating verses; to intone; to raise a song; IIp to be chanted; to humble oneself; IIIa to lead (in singing); to raise a shout; to cause to be occupied.
ܫܽܘܪܳܝܳܐ beginning, origin; preface; introductory prayer, anthem; Gram. subject.
ܕܒܰܪ fut. ܢܶܕܒܰܪ, imp. ܕܒܽܘܪ, Ia to lead, take, guide; to govern, manage; Ip; IIa to lead, guide; to manage, rule; to drive, steer; to plough; IIp to conduct oneself; to be governed, led, guided.
English: to lead, take; to govern, manage

long_definition: ܬܰܘܕܺܝܬܳܐ acknowledgement, thanksgiving, confession (of faith), religion.
ܣܓܶܕ fut. ܢܶܣܓܽܘܕ, Ia to do obeisance; to reverence, to venerate, to worship; Ip; IIp to prostrate oneself; IIIa to make to venerate.

ܦܪܰܩ fut. ܢܶܦܪܽܘܩ, Ia to separate, to depart, to withdraw; to ransom, to redeem, to save; Ip; IIa to break off, to dislocate, to take away; IIp to be rid of; to be torn away; to be delivered; IIIa to send off, to set apart, to remove.
ܡܺܐܡܪܳܐ speech, discourse, homily (prose or verse), treatise, Kth. poem.

ܪܕܳܐ fut. ܢܶܪܕܶܐ, Ia to travel, proceed, journey; to chastise; to instruct; ܪܕܶܐ educated, cultured; Ip to be chastised, disciplined, instructed; IIIa to supply abundantly; to make to flow; to chastise.
ܝܽܘܠܦܳܢܳܐ learning, instruction, study; teaching, doctrine.
ܦܬܰܚ fut. ܢܶܦܬܰܚ, Ia to open; Ip; IIa to open (eyes of the blind; a window etc.); IIp to be opened; to be captured.
ܡܗܰܝܡܢܳܐ believer, faithful, trustworthy; eunuch; Christian.
ܡܛܳܐ fut. ܢܶܡܛܶܐ, Ia reach, arrive at; happen, befall; IIa = Ia; IIp to attain to; IIIa to bring.
ܦܝܣ* Ip ܐܶܬܛܦܺܝܣ, ܐܶܬܬܦܺܝܣ to be persuaded, to obey; IIIa ܐܰܦܺܝܣ to urge, to petition, to persuade; to instruct; to intercede.
ܚܰܝܽܘܬܳܐ life, vitality; lifetime; living creature; animal.
ܨܰܘܡܳܐ fast, abstinence; ܨܰܘܡܳܐ ܪܰܒܳܐ Lent.
ܣܪܳܐ & ܣܪܺܝ fut. ܢܶܣܪܶܐ, Ia to be putrid, corrupt; Ip to become rotten; IIa to cause to rot; to make foul, to defile; IIIa to leave to putrefy.
ܛܶܟܣܳܐ (and ܛܰܟܣܳܐ) rank, order, series; rule, regulation; rite; equipment, apparatus; Kth. ܛܰܟܣܳܐ system.
ܬܰܪܥܺܝܬܳܐ mind, intelligence; opinion, thought; sense.
ܐܽܘܣܺܝܰܐ f. essence, substance, being; property, wealth.

ܒܛܶܠ fut. ܢܶܒܛܰܠ, Ia to cease (work), to be idle, at leisure; to come to an end, fail, cease; Ip -ܐܶܬܒܛܶܠ ܠ‍ to take care of, see to; IIa to bring to an end, abolish; IIp to cease, fail, be brought to an end.
English: to cease (work); to come to an end

long_definition: -ܐܰܟܡܳܐ ܕ as long as; ܐܰܟܡܳܐ ܙܰܒ̈ܢܺܝܢ sometimes.
ܡܫܰܡܫܳܢܳܐ minister, attendant; deacon; efficient; servant.
ܝܰܡܺܝܢܳܐ f. right, right hand; pledge, promise.

ܫܢܳܐ fut. ܢܶܫܢܶܐ, Ia to go away, leave; to change; to be dislocated; Ip to rage, rave; IIa to alter; to remove; to transfer; to depart; to migrate; to pass away, die IIp to be changed; to depart; to be taken away; to be translated; to become mad.
English: to go away; to be dislocated

long_definition: ܟܺܝܬ that is to say, indeed.
ܚܰܟܺܝܡܳܐ wise, sage, sensible; learned; clever, crafty.
ܣܳܟܳܐ end, extremity; sum, total; ܠܳܐ ܣܳܟ not at all; ܕܠܳܐ ܣܳܟ unending, endless.
ܓܰܒܳܐ side, edge; party; ܥܰܠ ܓܶܢ̱ܒ beside.
ܫܶܢܳܐ f. tooth; crag; spike, prong; ܫܶܢ̈ܶܐ teeth; ܫܶܢ̈ܳܬܳܐ prongs.
ܦܶܬܓܳܡܳܐ word, phrase, expression, sentence; versicle.
ܕܽܘܒܳܪܳܐ way of life, conduct, course; regimen, diet; administration; norm.

ܚܫܰܒ fut. ܢܶܚܫܽܘܒ, Ia to count, reckon, number; to enumerate; to think, take account of; to ascribe, impute; Ip to be numbered, imputed, accounted; to think; IIa to count; IIp to think, reckon, have in mind; to plan, devise.
English: to count; to think; to ascribe

long_definition: ܐܶܒܰܕ fut. ܢܺܐܒܰܕ, Ia to perish, be lost; Ip; IIIa ܐܰܘܒܶܕ destroy.
ܥܰܡܠܳܐ toil, labor; weariness; administrative district.
ܚܽܘܫܳܒܳܐ thinking, thought, idea, opinion, intention.
ܕܚܶܠ fut. ܢܶܕܚܰܠ, Ia to fear, stand in awe of, to revere; to be afraid (of); IIa IIIa to frighten, terrify.
English: to fear, stand in awe of

long_definition: ܪܰܒܽܘܬܳܐ greatness, size, majesty, magnificence; many phrases with ܪܰܒܽܘܬ e.g.:
ܫܰܒܬܳܐ (pl. ܫܰܒ̈ܶܐ) f. Saturday; Sabbath; week.
ܚܢܳܢܳܐ pity, mercy, compassion; favor, grace.
ܥܡܰܪ fut. ܢܶܥܡܰܪ, Ia to dwell, inhabit; to live; Ip to be inhabited; IIa, IIIa to cause to dwell, to settle; IIIp.
ܦܪܰܫ fut. ܢܶܦܪܽܘܫ, Ia to separate; to distinguish; to depart; Ip; IIa to explain; to part asunder; to distinguish; IIp to be separated; to be assigned; IIIa to set apart.
ܢܺܝܫܳܐ sign, emblem, banner; aim, purpose; subject matter, topic; meter; category.
ܕܳܢ fut. ܢܕܽܘܢ, Ia to judge, to administer justice; to go to law; to debate (with); Ip, IIIp to be judged; to contend with.
ܫܶܠܝܳܐ stillness, quiet, calm; ܡܶܢ ܫܶܠܝ̱ suddenly, unexpectedly; ܕܠܳܐ ܫܶܠܝܳܐ ceaselessly.
ܕܡܳܐ fut. ܢܶܕܡܶܐ, Ia to be like, resemble; Ip to be like, imitate; IIa to liken, compare; to imitate; IIp to become like; to be compared; to imitate; to imagine; to be likely.
ܐܳܬܳܐ (pl. ܐܳܬܘ̈ܳܬܳܐ) f. sign, token, miracle.
ܝܺܚܺܝܕܳܝܳܐ, ܐܺܝܚܺܝܕܳܝܳܐ sole, only, only-begotten; solitary, hermit; singular; specific, special; property, quality.
ܡܢܳܬܳܐ (pl. ܡܢܰܘ̈ܳܬܳܐ) part, portion, lot; relic; ܡܢܰܘ̈ܳܬܳܐ ܡܦܰܣ̈ܩܳܬܳܐ fragments.
ܕܰܝܪܳܐ m. habitation, dwelling; sheepfold; f. (pl. ܕܰܝܪ̈ܳܬܳܐ) monastery.
ܝܰܘܡܳܢ, ܝܰܘܡܳܢܳܐ today; at the present time.
ܫܳܥܬܳܐ (pl. ܫ̈ܳܥܶܐ) f. hour; moment; ܕܫܳܥܬܳܐ for now, for the moment; ܒܰܪ ܫܳܥܬܶܗ, ܒܳܗ̇ ܒܫܳܥܬܳܐ immediately, at once.
ܥܽܘܡܪܳܐ life; manner of life; habitation; monastery.
ܟܪܙ* Ip ܐܶܬܟܪܶܙ to be proclaimed; IIa to proscribe; IIIa to proclaim, preach; to execrate, disinherit publicly.
ܠܒܶܫ fut. ܢܶܠܒܰܫ, Ia to put on; to take on, assume; Ip to clothe oneself, to be clothed; IIIa to clothe.
English: to put on; to take on, assume

long_definition: ܪܶܓܠܳܐ f. foot, hoof, Kth. leg; ܪ̈ܶܓܠܳܬܳܐ bases.
